  "prompt": "Why does Peter Thiel hate Gawker?",
  "response": "Peter Thiel's animosity towards Gawker Media, specifically Gawker.com, stems from a 2007 article published by the site. The article, titled \"Peter Thiel is totally gay, people,\" publicly outed Thiel as gay, which he had not previously disclosed publicly. Thiel felt that this was an invasion of his privacy and believed the article was unnecessarily cruel.\n\nIn response to this incident, Thiel secretly funded multiple lawsuits against Gawker Media, including the high-profile case involving Hulk Hogan (Terry Bollea), who sued Gawker for posting a sex tape involving him. The lawsuit resulted in a $140 million judgment against Gawker, leading to the company's bankruptcy and eventual sale.\n\nThiel's actions against Gawker were motivated by his belief that the media company engaged in bullying and unethical journalism practices. He aimed to use the legal system to hold Gawker accountable and deter similar behavior from other media outlets.",
